  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0ba9 \u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf: \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Chinese ship echoes: Tight security in Tamil Nadu",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Security has been increased in the coastal areas of Tamil Nadu after a Chinese research ship anchored at Hambantota port yesterday (16).",
        "Surveillance operations have been intensified across the sea area of \u200b\u200bRamanathapuram district including Rameswaram, Pampan, Mandapam, Dhanushkodi.",
        "It is reported that 8 ships, 2 aircraft and 3 helicopters belonging to the Indian Navy and the Indian Coast Guard are engaged in non-stop patrolling in the waters of the Pakku Strait and the Gulf of Mannar in Ramanathapuram district. (a)"
      ],
